As you open the book to the page regarding Magi, you are blinded by a bright
flash of white light.  Once it subsides, the word "MAGI" glows on the page
in bright blue letters.  Magically, they disappear, and replacing that is
black handwriting describing the guild:

Magi are good, peaceful people.  They are very adept in the use of magic both
for defensive and offensive skills.  A Mage is not someone who you should
take lightly, for you might just get burned.  However, they are an invaluable
companion when it comes to partying.  With their extensive array of firepower,
they can help bring a party from near-extinction to victory very quickly.

Since Magi rely on magic a great deal, Intelligence is of utmost importance.
However, do not count out the other stats, for all will help you in your
travels.  Magi cannot wear large armours or shields, as it would stop them
from performing their magical abilities.

Do not worry about having to make a difficult choice when it comes to guilds.
With the Magi, there are no worries, and it's a choice you will not regret.

For information regarding the Magi, go to the guild hall w,w,w,w,w,s from cot,
and type "magehelp".  Or, alternately, talk to Aiken or any existing member
of the Magi.
